\i\b \cf0 Instructions for Mac
\i0\b0 \
\
Once the SpaceviewLive folder is copied somewhere on your mac:\
\
1- Double click on install.command.\
\
   A folder /photos/ is created and the photos are downloaded inside.\
   Every 30 minutes the script will check for an update on the DSCOVR website.\
\
2- With MacOSX, in order to put these pictures as wallpaper and make it refresh automatically:\
	- Open \'91System Preferences\'92\
	- Click on \'91Desktop & Screen Saver\'92\
	- Click on the \'91Desktop\'92 tab\
	- Click on the \'91+\'92 on the left-hand side and add the /photos/ folder\
	- Select the checkbox \'91Change picture\'92 and select 15 minutes (or lower)\
	- Select \'91Adapt to Screen\'92 and change the background color to black.\
	- You can select \'91Random order\'92, it works independently of this.\
	- In a very similar way you can create an awesome screen saver!\
\
3- Enjoy the view!\
\
\
Note: The reason why there are always two identical photos in the /photos/ folder is because if there was only one photo with always the same filename, MacOS does not refresh it.\
\
