\i\b Instructions for other systems
\i0\b0 \
\
1- Put the files DSCOVR.py and install_shell.sh in a folder.\
\
2- Access that folder with the terminal and run the shell script with:\
./install_shell.sh\
   A folder /photos/ is created and the photos are downloaded inside.\
   Every 30 minutes the script will check for an update on the DSCOVR website.\
\
3- From the terminal, the list of active crone jobs can be checked with:\
crontab -l\
\
4- Select the /photos/ folder in your wallpaper preferences (the precise way depends on the system).\
\
\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\'97\

\i\b Uninstall
\i0\b0 \
\
Simply cancel all the files contained in the package.\
\
To remove the automatic download open crone and cancel the line with the job.\
	- A good way to do this is write this in a terminal window:\
	env EDITOR=nano crontab -e\
	- Cancel the job\
	- Save the file by pressing Control + O, then Enter to accept\
	- Exit nano by pressing Control + X \
\
